Shanghai to Expand New Materials Industry
SHANGHAI , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Shanghai expects to raise 1.6 billion U.S. dollars to propel development of the new - materials industry in this oriental metropolis .
According to local sources , the city recently published a list of 28 investment programs detailing opportunities in Shanghai 's new-materials industry .
These programs have been worked out by a number of large state-owned enterprises which intend to cooperate with multinational corporations to develop new materials , with the Pudong New Area as the investment base .
The investment programs will focus on the development of electronics , new metals , and new organic , inorganic and synthetic materials such as polyformaldehyde and resin , according to sources .
